It looks to me that the pounding process releases more of the oils/scent of the herb simply because it is bruised on its entire surface as opposed to being cut/chopped which only makes smaller pieces.</p>
<p>I am pounding the dayligh out of all my herbs, or garlick in my stone mortar and pestle that I cannot live without.</p>
